Here V is the membrane potential of the neuron as a function of time , 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau_{m}$
\end_inset

is the membrane time constant, 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{rest}$
\end_inset

is the resting membrane potential, 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{ex}$
\end_inset

is the excitatory reversal potential and 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{in}$
\end_inset

is the inhibitory reversal potential.
 The synaptic conductances are expressed by 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{ex}$
\end_inset

(excitatory) and 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{inh}$
\end_inset

(inhibitory).
 They are modelled according to the following equations:
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\tau_{ex}\frac{dg_{ex}}{dt}=-g_{ex}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


