\begin_layout Section
The three-factor plasticity learning rule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here we introduce a learning rule based on evidence that STDP has been observed
 in the locust mushroom bodies (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Cassenaer:2007go"

\end_inset

).
 In this dopamine modulated STDP model, pre-post firing times create a temporal
 'tag' in the participating synapses,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\text{d}tag_{ij}(t)}{\text{d}t}=A_{+}x_{j}(t)S_{i}(t)-A_{-}y_{i}(t)S_{j}(t),
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{+}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $A,$
\end_inset

 determine the amplitude of maximum potentiation and depression that the
 tag can undergo.
 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{i}(t)$
\end_inset

 is the spike train of the i-th neuron, given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
S_{i}(t)=\sum_{k}\delta(t-t_{i,k}^{*}),
\end{equation}

\end_inset


