\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 is the i-th neuron and 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 is the index of the spike.
 The tag increases when the postsynaptic neuron fires an action potential
 and depends on the timing of the last spike timings of the presynaptic
 neuron through the variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{ij}(t)$
\end_inset

