\begin_layout Chapter
Discussion 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
* we are testing the fly in a simplified paradigm.
 cite: abbott for poisson, discussion of artificial stimuli 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have begun work that brings us closer to a model that can describe the
 mechanistic interactions between the eleements of the fly valence learning
 circuti.
 I aim to explore how sparse odour information stored in a balanced spiking
 network can be read by the output neurons through a multifactor learning
 rule.
 In the future we would like to expand our model with features such as:
 MBON-DA feedback, explicitly modelling KCs depending on the lobe they belong
 to, to create a state of the art model of the olfactory circuit that can
 give an account for learning a stimulus from the first layer together with
 transformation that occur until the the odour representation reaches the
 layer that controls behaviour.
 This will mean building a circuit that models antennae (ORNs), the antennal
 lobe (PNs) & the mushroom bodies( KCs, MBONs and DAs).
\end_layout

